{"id":"pydantic_ai_testmodel_isolation_pattern","type":"pattern","fact":"pydantic-ai agents can be unit-tested offline via `agent.override(model=TestModel(call_tools=[...], custom_output_args=...))` context manager, which substitutes the LLM call while preserving validators, retries, and the full Agent.run contract.","recommendation":"For per-agent isolation tests, prefer `agent.override(model=TestModel(...))` over monkeypatching internal methods like `_run_pipeline`. To force tool dispatch in a lead/orchestrator agent, pass `call_tools=['run_market_access_research','run_analyst_research','run_reporter']`. Tests run in <1s with no Ollama required (see tests/test_pipeline_stages.py).","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"agent_pipeline_tdd_error_handling/iteration_02","date":"2026-05-24"}],"tags":["pydantic-ai","testing","testmodel","agents","offline-tests"],"affectedFiles":["tests/test_pipeline_stages.py","app/agents/*.py"],"createdAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z"}
